Description:

This property has plenty of day yards for horses, loose boxes and round yard. Stock yards with easy sorting yards, a huge dam and 3 enormous tradesman's sheds with concrete floors and a 60m x 20 metre unfinished Olympic size horse menage plus a lot more. Be quick on calling as this is a quality acreage property.

Address: 5050 SOUTH GIPPSLAND HIGHWAY Lang Lang VIC 3984
Description:
SUPERB LOCATION/ LIFESTYLE/GRAZING/FATTENING/BREEDING PROPERTY
Outstanding position with frontage to both South Gippsland Hwy and Bass Hwy and well positioned in the high growth/tourism region of Westernport Bay. Boasting water views across French Island and stunning rural country side.
Improvements consist of a country style 3 bedroom weatherboard home, hay and machinery shedding plus stockyards. The land is very gently undulating country with approximately 10 acres of natural bush and treed area with the balance pasture. The property is fenced to 6 main paddocks and watered by bore to troughs.
Ideally suited for cattle, horses, tourism, this excellent property is only 3km to Lang Lang, 20 minutes to Pakenham & Cranbourne, only 25 minutes to Kilcunda & Philip Island. Melbourne CBD approximately 1 hour.
If you would like to inspect this property or have any questions, please contact Scott Andersen on 0409 785 846 or Don Olden on 0417 805 312.

Description:
SUBSTANTIAL BRICK HOME WITH SPECTACULAR WESTERNPORT VIEWS
Located a stroll away from a quiet sandy beach in Grantville is this imposing light filled, brick home which presents beautifully. If youve been seeking a spacious home with a killer view, you wont go past this one.
Perched up high on the block to maximise the view, there is a ground floor bonus area, perfect for a cellar and roomy enough to secure storage of all your beach, play and garden equipment out of the weather.
Level one comprises a large open plan living area, modern kitchen and dining area, bedroom with sea and French Island views. This area is the ideal family entertainment zone, with it's attached secure deck, ideal for the largest outdoor setting and barbeque, all situated to take in the view and the gorgeous sea breeze. A very large laundry offers built in cupboards and easy care tiled floors. There is a full length covered deck at the rear of the home and ample room for a big vegie patch and safe fencing for pets.
Level two doesnt disappoint, with another very large living area and a substantial deck inviting you outside to take in yet a better view. A further 2 bedrooms with BIRs and spacious bathroom complete the top level in the home.
The home is all electric and has 3 x split system air-conditioners, a hot water service to both the house and the garage and a cook top with separate oven and dishwasher.
Outside is a separate brick garage with attached carport, sink with hot and cold water connected, perfect for cleaning fish caught off the beach in Stewart Street and ideal for cleaning up after gardening.
This home is ideal as a permanent home but would also lend itself to holiday makers and holiday letting, the gardens are mature and very low maintenance and the property is securely fenced. The home is freshly painted throughout and has new carpets and offers a turn key purchase, just move in and start living your relaxed beach lifestyle.

Description:
Breathtaking Bay Views - 2 Storey Stunner
In a well established quiet area of Grantville is this 2 storey 3 bedroom double brick home with weatherboard cladding. This home has been recently renovated and tastefully decorated. The European kitchen has modern appliances with high spec units, plenty of storage, an electric cooker with induction cook top & 2 ring gas burner making this a fantastic usable space. There are spectacular views of Westernport Bay including French Island and as far as the Dandenong Ranges from both the rear lower level entertaining deck and upper floor balcony.
This property also offers a double carport to the front of the property with another carport and garage/workshop to the rear so there's plenty of room for a boat or caravan. This lovely property has been priced to sell so be quick to call to arrange an inspection.

THE ULTIMATE IN MODERN BAYSIDE LIVING
Immaculately presented and in a prized position this elegant home is only 6 years old and appears in brand new condition, in the popular up and coming zone of Corinella. The home features a spacious lounge flowing into the tiled dining area leading to a kitchen with modern appliances and reverse cycle air conditioning. There are 3 spacious bedrooms with built-ins & carpet throughout. The well-appointed master suite also includes ensuite, walk in wardrobe and reverse cycle air conditioning. There is a large outdoor entertaining area with beautifully maintained gardens and a fully enclosed backyard. Remote control double garage with through access to backyard.
With the foreshore at the end of the street, walking tracks & 24 hour boat ramp only minutes away this home delivers a premium coastal lifestyle. Easy access to the General Store, park, community centre, tennis courts, primary school, kindergarten, all bus services & only 90 minutes from Melbourne CBD.

Description:
BEACHSIDE WITH SOLAR ON STEWART!
This gem of a home is in a very quiet part of Grantville and enjoys a short cut from Stewart Street straight onto the sandy beach. It's a bit of hidden secret where locals walk to the beach leaving cars and parking problems behind. The house is a roomy 3 bedroom beach house with good old fashioned sized rooms which have been improved by the current owners. There is new carpeting, a full en-suite bathroom to the master, timber lined ceilings and a new dine-in kitchen. Some new aluminium windows and decking have also been replaced. Best of all, the house has a solar system with bills of only $45-$50 received per month in recent months. Outside there is parking under the carport which adjoins a very large garage which has both power and water connected. This home will suit either permanent living or use as a holiday home and being 100 metres to the beach path has to be a bonus. 'Beach photos attached are of the actual beach at Deep Creek/Stewart St'

Just two doors down from the main street with foodworks, IGA, bakery, restaurants, pharmacy, doctors and primary school, and Dick Jones Reserve right across the road with tennis courts and open parkland - all within moments walk away! So convenient to everything, living the country lifestyle in this beautiful part of South Gippsland, will be every bit of the tree-change you had hoped for.
Perfect for first home buyers, investors, lifestyle seekers and retirees, this solid, beautifully built, double brick home on a large 736sqm block was originally the local council water authority office - built in 1978, the very unique property has since been transformed into a loving home.
Make no mistake, this grand old dame showcases a design and quality far ahead of its era! 10ft timber panelled ceilings, huge floor-to-ceiling picture windows, wide open spaces and openings, built in units, shelves and benches showcase throughout the huge home - and gorgeous landscaped gardens surrounding the outside.
The enormous master bedroom could easily be divided into two, or perhaps have a walk in robe and ensuite incorporated in. Bathroom and toilet as well as a second toilet and basin. Two separate living zones with a wood heater and split system air con in the lounge room plus a spacious family room and a galley-style kitchen with plenty of storage.
Outside, there’s a large shed with concrete floor and power, a carport, AND, bonus back entrance! Perfect for the lifestyle seeker, traveller, fisherman, tradesman and handyman!
The bones of this beautiful home are truly magic and the options are plenty. No matter what your plans for it are, once inside, you will truly appreciate what’s already here and any future renovations are sure to pay tribute to its striking features! Be quick before you miss out!

Address: 85 Gurdies-St Helier rd The Gurdies VIC 3984
Description:
PEACEFUL RETREAT ON 5 ACRES
THE GURDIES:
The minute you arrive at this gorgeous property you will instantly feel relaxed and shift into holiday mode, whether you make it your holiday home, weekend retreat or secluded sanctuary, the features which you will discover on inspection will meet all your needs.
Positioned on a private 5-acre allotment, the property offers a mixture of expansive open lawn areas, indigenous grasses, majestic messmates and cottage gardens guaranteed to create a haven for the abundant wildlife including the king parrots and rosellas who call this area home.
The cedar constructed home offers a unique roof line, with external balcony and decked areas creating fantastic outdoor spaces to enjoy all year round. Spread over three levels, on entering the home you will discover a spacious open living space filled with natural light, featuring huge timber lined vaulted ceiling and includes combustion heating perfect to enjoy as the days and nights become cooler. The timber kitchen is filled with character combined with quality appliances and ample bench space, adjacent is the spacious dining room perfect for family gatherings both formal and casual, this is a home which will attract visitors from far and wide so be prepared to entertain!
Also on this level are two double bedrooms, family bathroom and laundry facilities. From every room downstairs, there are different views of the surrounding garden with subtle changes throughout the year to enjoy. Hardwood timber floors throughout adds further character.
Moving upstairs you discover an open space currently being used as the master retreat complete with walk in robe, ensuite and adjacent living area, perfect for a parents retreat, study or reading nook. Direct access to the balcony offers distant views to Western Port Bay as well as the opportunity to enjoy the ever-changing tree vistas.
With rambling pathways to discover outside, this property truly is a haven to enjoy, extra bonus features include 55,000 L tanks ready for you to enjoy the freshness of rainwater, large open carport with mezzanine perfect for extra storage needs, separate workshop, wood shed and secure fencing.
The Gurdies is a tightly held area and is located just past Koo Wee Rup and Lang Lang . If you like bushwalking, mountain bike riding, horse riding, bird watching or just plain kicking back and relaxing, this is the place for you. Wineries abound in the region and wildlife is plentiful. The sunsets over Western Port Bay and French Island are to die for.
The drive to Phillip Island, Wonthaggi, Cranbourne and Pakenham is only ½ hour with easy access to the Melbourne train service, with no traffic jams until you hit suburbia. does it sound like a nice escape?
Whether its enjoying a drink on the veranda, listening to the rain on the roof or watching your children actually climb a tree this gorgeous property will appeal on many levels.
At Ray White Cranbourne our price indications are based upon probable market value, the likely selling price and vendor expectations. You can view with confidence that vendors will sell within the range with favourable conditions.

Description:
GIDDY UP ON 5 ACRES
Located just down the road from Woolami Race track is this 5 acre property currently divided into paddocks for horses.
With mains water as well as tank water, you wont have to worry about skimping on watering stock, washing your horses, vehicles or for establishing a garden.
The house is hardi-plank construction with a colorbond roof and is a classic homestead style home with its trademark wide verandah across the front. Currently a blank canvas, the home has the potential to shine with some cosmetic changes like painting and floor coverings.
Entering the home through the period style lead light front door, the master suite with walk in robe and ensuite is located opposite a spacious formal lounge room with wood heating. These rooms enjoy a fabulous view towards the green hills with wide windows sheltered by the full length front verandah.
With a timber lined vaulted ceiling in the family area adjoining the spacious modern kitchen you get a real feeling of space for the largest family gathering.
The three remaining bedrooms with a family bathroom are located privately to the other end of the home and enjoy a beautiful view towards the hills beyond Woolamai.
Outside there is a large garden shed and a concrete slab has been laid for a large machinery shed or stable block. The home has solar panels installed to minimise your utility charges.
Inspection by appointment.

INVEST NOW - CORNER BLOCK !!!
Positioned in a great location on the corner of Smythe St and Burchell Close is this flat 627 sqm approx block which is only a couple of minutes from the 24 hour boat ramp, pier and jetty.
Build a new home for holidaying or for permanent living in amongst the quality homes already established in the estate. From a two-storey dwelling you may capture some glimpses of the bay. This property may be suitable for future development STCA.
Within walking distance to shop, community centre, park, bus service, tennis courts, lawn bowls, hall etc. The local primary school and kindergarten plus a great local cafe are only a few minutes away or visit the local wineries and group of local shops approximately 8 mins away. Corinella has some very picturesque coastal walks.
